Whenever, in the course of the daily hunt, the red hunter comes upon a scene
that is strikingly beautiful or sublime -- a black thundercloud with the
rainbowâ€™s glowing arch above the mountain; a white waterfall in the heart of a
green gorge; a vast prairie tinged with the blood-red of sunset -- he pauses
for an instant in the attitude of worship.
